<TITLE> BCL and lefts team up against Shibir </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi University, Feb (bdnews24.com)  Four student organisations of Rajshahi University on Friday jointly formed 'Osamprodayik-Gonotantrik Chhatra Sangram Parishad' to 'eradicate' Islami Chhatra Shibir from the university campus. The parishad leaders said the combined forum would launch its activities on Feb 21 with a demonstration against Shibir, student wing of the fundamentalist Jamaat-e-Islami, a major ally of the main opposition. The combined forum comprises of pro-Awami League student organisation Bangladesh Chhatra League, Jatiya Samajtantrik Dal backed student wing, wihch is also called Bangladesh Chhatra League, Workers' Party wing Bangladesh Chhatra Maitri and Communist Party of Bangladesh backed Bangladesh Chhatra Union. BCL university unit president Awal Kabir and general secretary Mazedul Islam told reporters that Shibir would be 'eradicated' from the RU campus at any cost. Chhatra Maitri convener Mazharul Islam said all four student organisations of this joint forum 'believe in the spirit of the Liberation War'. Chhatra Union president Rafi Ahmed Chanchal said Shibir would be easily 'evicted' from the campus if the students united. bdne
